Package: tailscale-receiver
Architecture: all
Depends: tailscale, systemd, coreutils, findutils, netcat-openbsd | netcat-traditional | socat, procps, util-linux
Recommends: notify-send, kdialog | zenity | whiptail, dolphin | nautilus
Suggests: clamav, apparmor
Description: Automated Tailscale file receiver service
 Tailscale Receiver automatically accepts and processes files sent via
 Tailscale's Taildrop feature. It runs as a systemd service and provides
 desktop notifications when files are received.
 .
 Features include:
  - Automatic file reception with ownership correction
  - Directory support with recursive permissions
  - Configurable polling intervals and health monitoring
  - File integrity verification with checksums
  - GNOME/KDE desktop integration
  - Comprehensive logging and health monitoring
  - Enterprise-grade configuration management
 .
 This package is designed for Linux systems using systemd and provides
 both continuous service mode and power-efficient timer mode for
 battery-powered devices.